reviewText: This video is a lot of fun -- partly because whiny little Elmo doesn't dominate, but mostly because the material is so darn good.  As advertised, this is a set of some of the silliest songs "Sesame Street" has to offer.  Anything with the Honkers in it is fine by me! (Joe Sixpack, ReadThatAgain kid's reviews)
summary: One of the best Sesame Street DVDs

reviewText: I think some of these skits were made before I was born! My daughter still enjoyed watching the video, but man. I felt like I time warped back a few decades. Needless to say, don't expect the newer characters in this video. I think they plopped Elmo in there for a (maybe) 10 second bit?

Title: N/A

reviewText: My son, Christian, is nearly 19 years old.  I bought this video for him when he was about 2.  He could barely talk but he adored this video.  He memorized the words to all the songs.  He jumped and danced and twirled for hours.  I've since searched just to find this so that if I EVER have grandchildren, they can enjoy it just as much.  After I bought it, a neighbors child found it in my DVD cabinet and wanted it, so I gave it to him.  I'm now buying it for my great-nieces for Christmas as they are BIG Elmo fans.  It may seem just a little dated as the clothing isn't exactly the latest fashion, but I don't think the kids would notice one bit!  I can even still remember the words!!

reviewText: I have to admit that I am the type of parent who believes that the majority of children's toys, videos, etc. should have a great deal of educational value, so I did not buy this dvd for my 2 year old, my mother (aka Grandma of the Universe) did.  Even though I was quick to frown upon this addition to our collection including "Learning About Letters" and "1,2,3 Count with Me," my heart was melted immediately after seeing my little sweet-heart dancing away for half an hour to the songs featured on this program.  My son enjoys this show so much and I am so happy to be reminded that a lot of time, kids just want to have fun...so let them!
summary: Turns My Son into a Dancing Machine!

reviewText: This is an awesome video, one of my all-time favorites for children. It contains my very favorite song about the number ten, the one that goes "ten tiny turtles on the telephone." All the other songs are fantastic as well. My daughter actually gets tired of watching this video before I do!

reviewText: This one doesn't flow as well as some of the other Sesame Street ones--this was my original comment, but as we watch it more and more, my daughter loves this video.  I want to give it more stars now that I am editing my review, but Amazon won't let me change that part.  This is a very cute video, and just took us more time than the others to get into.  My daughter loves the Honker Duckie Dinger Jamboree and Put Down the Duckie (with tons of celebrities like John Candy, Paul Simon, Danny DeVito, and Rhea Perlman to name a few).  A very good movie that all ages can enjoy (and MY mom's favorite because of the James Taylor song, too).  Buy this video!
summary: I wish I could change it to give it more stars!
